mastery.question_text:
$P$, $Q$ and $R$ are three vertices of a rectangle whose sides are parallel to the axes. Write the coordinates of the fourth vertex $S$.
[tikz]
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.6]
\draw[step=0.5,gray!18] (-4,-4) grid (4,4);
\draw[step=1,gray!40] (-4,-4) grid (4,4);
\draw[<->,thick] (-4.4,0)--(4.4,0) node[right] {$x$};
\draw[<->,thick] (0,-4.4)--(0,4.4) node[above] {$y$};
\foreach \x in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} \node[below,font=\scriptsize] at (\x,0) {$\x$};
\foreach \y in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} \node[left,font=\scriptsize] at (0,\y) {$\y$};
\draw[thick] (-2,1.5)--(2,1.5)--(2,-1.5);
\fill (-2,1.5) circle (2.2pt);
\node[above left,font=\footnotesize] at (-2,1.5) {$P$};
\fill (2,1.5) circle (2.2pt);
\node[above right,font=\footnotesize] at (2,1.5) {$Q$};
\fill (2,-1.5) circle (2.2pt);
\node[below right,font=\footnotesize] at (2,-1.5) {$R$};
\end{tikzpicture}
[/tikz]

mastery.solution_text:
$S$ is directly below $P$ and directly left of $R$.
$S$ shares $P$'s $x$-value: $x = -2$.
$S$ shares $R$'s $y$-value: $y = -1.5$.
$(-2, -1.5)$
[tikz]
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.6]
\draw[step=0.5,gray!18] (-4,-4) grid (4,4);
\draw[step=1,gray!40] (-4,-4) grid (4,4);
\draw[<->,thick] (-4.4,0)--(4.4,0) node[right] {$x$};
\draw[<->,thick] (0,-4.4)--(0,4.4) node[above] {$y$};
\foreach \x in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} \node[below,font=\scriptsize] at (\x,0) {$\x$};
\foreach \y in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4} \node[left,font=\scriptsize] at (0,\y) {$\y$};
\draw[thick] (-2,1.5)--(2,1.5)--(2,-1.5);
\draw[thick,dashed] (2,-1.5)--(-2,-1.5)--(-2,1.5);
\fill (-2,1.5) circle (2.2pt);
\node[above left,font=\footnotesize] at (-2,1.5) {$P$};
\fill (2,1.5) circle (2.2pt);
\node[above right,font=\footnotesize] at (2,1.5) {$Q$};
\fill (2,-1.5) circle (2.2pt);
\node[below right,font=\footnotesize] at (2,-1.5) {$R$};
\fill (-2,-1.5) circle (2.2pt);
\node[below left,font=\footnotesize] at (-2,-1.5) {$S$};
\end{tikzpicture}
[/tikz]

